nt||at|bseagram:  South counts losers.   One diamond and one potential heart loser
That's too many
The hand is fairly evenly divided which makes for a great possibility for the "Strip and Throw in"
There are 4 suits,   trump suit...draw as many as possible
Strip suits, the Clubs in this case.   Easy suit, no problems with this suit but strip completely
With the strip suit, if you have an extra club in hand you must trump in dummy
or an extra club in dummy, have to ruff in hand|
pg| ***** 30 ***** |


nt||at|bseagram: Just like when you get into shower, you have to strip completely!!!
So, next is the DO NOT TOUCH suit...in this case Hearts.   Vow to not touch this suit 
Then next is the EXIT suit, in this case Diamonds...this is the suit with which you will THROW THEM IN
So when you are in a contract that depends on a finesse, think of the strip and throw in and whether you can do it.
WIN @dAce at trick 1 ...draw 2 rounds of trump and then play all clubs and then STOP
(MM: You can follow Barbara's notes by clicking on the cards or try at the end of the notes)|
