nt||at|bseagram: Now play @D and one of opponents will win  (the @d is your EXIT suit). 
At this point your LHO will give you a sluff and a ruff (or lead a @h for you). 
When given that opportunity (which is a declarer's dream come true, ALWAYS ruff in dummy and sluff from your hand  
On this hand, it does not matter where you ruffed and where you sluffed but often it will.
What if west had now led a @H instead after trick 7???? |
